```class Solution {
public:
    int appendCharacters(string s, string t) {
        int j = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            if (j < t.size() && c == t[j]) {
                j++;
            }
        }
        return t.size() - j;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(s.length)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the string s and increments a pointer j in string t whenever a match is found, effectively finding the longest common subsequence. The remaining characters in t are the minimum number of characters that need to be appended to s.

